  "text": "Round of 16 · 7 July 2026 · Vancouver. Final score: Switzerland 0–0 Colombia. Switzerland outlasted Colombia across a goalless night and won the shootout to reach their first quarter-final since 1954.\n\nSeventy-two years of hurt sat on Swiss shoulders; ninety minutes, extra time and twelve yards would decide whether it finally lifted.\n\nNo goals were recorded in normal or extra time; the tie was resolved from twelve yards.\n\nNeither side could find a way through in ninety minutes or extra time; chances came and went at both ends without reward. The shootout brought the drama the open play had withheld. Davinson Sánchez rattled his spot-kick against the bar and Gregor Kobel saved smartly from Cucho Hernández, before Rubén Vargas held his nerve to send Switzerland through 4-3. For a nation that had waited generations, this was catharsis — and a quarter-final date with the champions to come.\n\nMomentum, as ever in the knockouts, proved a fragile and fleeting thing.\n\nThe expected-goals picture tightened around every set piece and transition.\n\nFor the record, Switzerland advanced. Goal, team and minute for every event above are Merkle-proven on Solana devnet via TxLINE; the scorer names are attributed from public match reports and aligned to the verified goals by team and order. Nothing here rests on the commentator's word alone.",
